Gradient Descent for Unconstrained Minimization

Riddhiman Das

Problem 1: Linear Regression Loss

n <- 100
x <- rnorm(n, mean = 1, sd = sqrt(2))
noise <- rnorm(n, mean = 0, sd = sqrt(5))
y <- 2 + 3 * x + noise
X <- cbind(1, x)

loss <- function(beta) {
  sum((y - X %*% beta)^2) / (2 * n)
}

gradient <- function(beta) {
  - (t(X) %*% (y - X %*% beta)) / n
}

beta <- c(0, 0)
eta <- 0.01
eps <- 1e-6
iter <- 10000

loss_list <- numeric(iter)
beta_history <- matrix(NA, nrow = iter, ncol = 2)

for (i in seq(iter)) {
  g <- as.vector(gradient(beta))
  loss_list[i] <- loss(beta)
  beta_history[i, ] <- beta
  
  if (sqrt(sum(g^2)) < eps) {
    cat("Converged at iteration", i, "\n")
    loss_list <- loss_list[1:i]
    beta_history <- beta_history[1:i, , drop = FALSE]
    break
  }
  beta <- beta - eta * g
  if (i == iter) cat("Reached max iterations")
}
## Converged at iteration 1838
cat("Estimated beta:", round(beta, 4), "\n")
## Estimated beta: 1.827 3.2357
cat("True beta: 2, 3\n")
## True beta: 2, 3

This is close to the true \(\beta=(2,3)\).

beta0_grid <- seq(min(beta_history[ ,1]) - 1, max(beta_history[ ,1] + 1), length.out = 100)
beta1_grid <- seq(min(beta_history[ ,2]) - 1, max(beta_history[ ,2] + 1), length.out = 100)

loss_matrix <- outer(beta0_grid, beta1_grid, Vectorize(function(b0, b1) loss(c(b0, b1))))

filled.contour(beta0_grid, beta1_grid, loss_matrix,
               color.palette = cm.colors,
               plot.axes = {
                 axis(1); axis(2);
                 lines(beta_history[, 1], beta_history[, 2], col = "red", lwd = 2);
                 points(beta_history[1, 1], beta_history[1, 2], pch = 21, bg = "green", cex = 1.5);
                 points(2, 3, pch = 4, col = "blue", lwd = 3);
                 points(beta[1], beta[2], pch = 4, col = "orange", lwd = 3)
               },
               xlab = expression(beta[0]), ylab = expression(beta[1]),
               main = "Loss vs Iteration")

plot(loss_list, type = "l", lwd = 2,
     xlab = "Iteration index", ylab = "Loss",
     main = "Loss vs Iterations")

Problem 2: Logistic Regression Negative Log-Likelihood

data <- read.csv("/home/riddhiman/Documents/opt_assignment_3/data-problem-2.csv")

X <- as.matrix(data[, c("x1", "x2")]) 
y <- data$y

loss <- function(beta) {
  sum(log(1 + exp(-y * (X %*% beta))))
}

gradient <- function(beta) {
  z <- X %*% beta
  yz <- y * z
  s <- plogis(yz)  # Sigmoid function
  term <- y * (1 - s)
  -as.vector(t(X) %*% term)
}

beta <- c(0, 0)
eta <- 0.05
eps <- 1e-5
iter <- 10000
loss_list <- numeric(iter)
beta_history <- matrix(NA, nrow = iter, ncol = 2)

for (i in seq(iter)) {
  g <- gradient(beta)
  loss_list[i] <- loss(beta)
  beta_history[i, ] <- beta
  
  if (sqrt(sum(g^2)) < eps) {
    loss_list <- loss_list[1:i]
    beta_history <- beta_history[1:i, ]
    cat("Converged at iteration", i, "\n")
    break
  }
  beta <- beta - eta * g
  if (i == iter) cat("Reached max iterations.", "\n")
}
## Converged at iteration 254
cat("Estimated beta:", beta, "\n")
## Estimated beta: 2.384688 -2.855388
beta0_grid <- seq(min(beta_history[,1]) - 1, max(beta_history[,1]) + 1, length.out = 100)
beta1_grid <- seq(min(beta_history[,2]) - 1, max(beta_history[,2]) + 1, length.out = 100)

loss_matrix <- outer(beta0_grid, beta1_grid, Vectorize(function(b0, b1) loss(c(b0, b1))))

filled.contour(
  beta0_grid, beta1_grid, loss_matrix,
  color.palette = cm.colors,
  plot.axes = {
    axis(1); axis(2)
    lines(beta_history[,1], beta_history[,2], col = "red", lwd = 2)
    points(beta_history[1,1], beta_history[1,2], pch = 21, bg = "green", cex = 1.5)
    points(tail(beta_history,1)[1], tail(beta_history,1)[2], pch = 4, col = "orange", lwd = 3)
  },
  xlab = expression(beta[0]), ylab = expression(beta[1]),
  main = "Logistic Regression Descent Path"
)

# Plot 2: Loss vs iterations
plot(loss_list, type = "l", lwd = 2,
     xlab = "Iteration", ylab = "Loss",
     main = "Loss vs Iteration")

Problem 3: Quadratic Convex Function

Note that \(x\) minimizes the function when \[f'(x)=2Ax+b=0\] i.e., \(x=[1,1]\).

This explains why our gradient-descent algorithm immediately terminates.

A <- matrix(c(2, 0, 0, 4), nrow = 2)
b <- c(-4, -8)

f <- function(x) {
  t(x) %*% A %*% x + sum(b * x)
}

gradient <- function(x) {
  2 * A %*% x + b
}

x <- c(1, 1)
eta <- 0.1
eps <- 1e-6
max_iter <- 1000
loss_history <- numeric(max_iter)
x_history <- matrix(NA, nrow = max_iter, ncol = 2)

for (i in 1:max_iter) {
  g <- gradient(x)
  loss_history[i] <- f(x)
  x_history[i, ] <- x
  
  if (sqrt(sum(g^2)) < eps) {
    cat("Converged at iteration", i, "\n")
    loss_history <- loss_history[1:i]
    x_history <- x_history[1:i, , drop = FALSE]
    break
  }
  x <- x - eta * g
}
## Converged at iteration 1
x1_grid <- seq(0.5, 1.5, length.out = 100)
x2_grid <- seq(0.5, 1.5, length.out = 100)
loss_matrix <- outer(x1_grid, x2_grid, Vectorize(function(a, b) f(c(a, b))))

filled.contour(x1_grid, x2_grid, loss_matrix,
               color.palette = cm.colors,
               plot.axes = {
                 axis(1); axis(2)
                 points(x_history[, 1], x_history[, 2], 
                        col = "red", pch = 20, cex = 1.5)
                 points(1, 1, pch = 4, col = "gold", lwd = 3)
               },
               xlab = expression(x[1]), ylab = expression(x[2]),
               main = "Quadratic Function Descent Path")

plot(f(c(1,1)), xlim=c(1,5), xlab = "Iteration Index", ylab = "Loss",
     main = "Loss vs Iteration",
     col = "darkblue")

Problem 4: Normal Distribution MLE (Negative Log-Likelihood)

x <- read.csv("/home/riddhiman/Documents/opt_assignment_3/data-problem-4.csv")

mu = 0
sigma = 1
eta <- 0.01
eps <- 1e-5
iter <- 10000

loss_list <- numeric(iter)
theta_history <- matrix(NA, nrow = iter, ncol = 2)

loss <- function(mu, sigma) {
  n*log(sigma) + (sum((x-mu)^2)/(2 * (sigma^2)))
}

gradient <- function(mu ,sigma) {
  grad_sigma <- (n / sigma) - (sum((x - mu)^2) / (sigma^3))
  grad_mu <- (sum(mu - x) / (sigma^2))
  c(grad_mu, grad_sigma)
}

for (i in 1:iter) {
  
  loss_list[i] <- loss(mu, sigma)
  theta_history[i,1] <- mu
  theta_history[i,2] <- sigma
  
  if (sqrt(sum(gradient(mu, sigma)^2))< eps) {
    theta_history <- theta_history[1:i, ]
    loss_list <- loss_list[1:i]
    cat("Converged at iteration", i, "\n")
    break
  }
  
  g <- gradient(mu, sigma)
  mu <- mu - eta * g[1]
  sigma <- sigma - eta * g[2]
  
  if(i == iter){
    cat("Reached maximum iterations", "\n")
  }
}
## Converged at iteration 474
cat("Estimated mu and sigma: ", theta_history[i,], "\n")
## Estimated mu and sigma:  5.013222 2.093897

The MLE of the mean is given by \[\hat{\mu} = \frac{1}{n}\sum_{i=1}^n x_i\]

mu_MLE <- sum(x)/n
cat("mu hat MLE: ", mu_MLE)
## mu hat MLE:  5.013222

and the MLE of the standard deviation is given by \[\hat{\sigma}= \sqrt{\frac{1}{n}\sum_{i=1}^n(x_i - \hat{\mu})^2}.\]

cat("sigma hat MLE: ", sqrt(sum((x-mu_MLE)^2)/n))
## sigma hat MLE:  2.093897
mu_grid <- seq(min(theta_history[,1]) - 1, max(theta_history[,1]) + 1, length.out = 100)
sigma_grid <- seq(min(theta_history[,2]) - 1, max(theta_history[,2]) + 1, length.out = 100)

loss_matrix <- outer(mu_grid, sigma_grid, loss)

filled.contour(mu_grid, sigma_grid, loss_matrix,
               color.palette = cm.colors,
               plot.axes = {
                 axis(1); axis(2)
                 lines(theta_history[, 1], theta_history[, 2], col = "red", lwd = 2)
                 points(theta_history[1,1], theta_history[1,2], pch = 21, bg = "green", cex = 1.5)
                 points(tail(theta_history,1)[1], tail(theta_history,1)[2], pch = 4, col = "orange", lwd = 3)
               },
               xlab = "mu", ylab = "sigma",
               main = "Normal Distribution's MLE descent path")

plot(loss_list, type = "l", lwd = 2, xlab = "Iteration Index", ylab = "Loss", 
     main = "Loss vs Iteration")

Problem 5: Rosenbrock Function (Non-Convex)

eta <- 0.001
eps <- 1e-6
iter <- 10000

x <- -1
y <- 1

loss_list <- numeric(iter)
theta_history <- matrix(NA, nrow = iter, ncol = 2)

loss <- function(x, y) {
  (1-x)^2 + 100 * (y - x^2)^2
}

gradient <- function(x,y) {
  e1 <- (-2 * (1 - x)) - (400 * x * (y - x^2)^2)
  e2 <- 200 * (y - x^2)
  c(e1, e2)
}

for (i in 1:iter) {
  loss_list[i] <- loss(x,y)
  theta_history[i,1] <- x
  theta_history[i,2] <- y
  
  if(sqrt(sum(gradient(x,y)^2)) < eps) {
    loss_list <- loss_list[1:i]
    theta_history <- theta_history[1:i, ]
    
    cat("Converged at iteration ", i, "\n")
    
    break
  }
  
  g <- gradient(x,y)
  x <- x - eta * g[1]
  y <- y - eta * g[2]
  
  if(i == iter)
    cat("Maximum iterations reached")
}
## Converged at iteration  8000
cat("Estimated values: ", theta_history[i, ], "\n")
## Estimated values:  0.9999998 0.9999996
x_grid <- seq(min(theta_history[ ,1]) - 1, max(theta_history[ ,2]) + 1, length.out = 100)
y_grid <- seq(min(theta_history[ ,2]) - 1, max(theta_history[ ,2]) + 1, length.out = 100)
  
z <- outer(x_grid, y_grid, loss)
  
filled.contour(x_grid, y_grid, z,
               color.palette = cm.colors,
               plot.axes = {
                 axis(1) 
                 axis(2)
                 lines(theta_history[ ,1], theta_history[ ,2], col = "red", lwd = 2)
                 points(theta_history[1,1], theta_history[1,2], pch = 21, bg = "green", cex = 1.5)
                 points(tail(theta_history,1)[1], tail(theta_history,1)[2], pch = 4, col = "orange", lwd = 3)
                 },
               xlab = "x", ylab = "y",
               main = "Descent path in the Rosenbrock Function")

plot(loss_list, type = "l", lwd = 2, xlab = "Iteration index", ylab = "Loss", 
     main = "Loss vs Iteration")
